The paper deals with a fundamental data structure problem in databases and computational geometry, which suggests that it belongs to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry) categories. The problem also has applications in databases, which makes cs.DB (Databases) another likely category. The paper discusses tradeoffs between query time and space, which is related to the cs.CC (Computational Complexity) category. Finally, the paper discusses cell probe lower bounds, which is related to the cs.IT (Information Theory) category.
